{"id":14881871,"mediaExerciseId":"828d12da-77a2-4818-9ec1-867f49888cd9","exerciseName":"14","chapterName":"24","chapterTitle":"Options and Corporate Finance","groupId":612498,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":823,"solutions":[{"id":5999982,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine why natural resource extraction facilities provide a good example of the value of the option to suspend operations.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define the option to suspend.\n\n**Option to suspend** is an option to shut down a project if the conditions are unfavorable and resume the operations when the conditions are favorable again.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3565ebe09028d23e0d2c2dc04f0695e1/70a92fa1f35941a050124c06049272c9/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3565ebe09028d23e0d2c2dc04f0695e1/70a92fa1f35941a050124c06049272c9/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"### Natural resource extraction facilities (such as oil wells or gold mines) provide a good example of the value of the option to suspend operations. \n\nThese types of facilities provide a good example of the value of the option to suspend operations because extraction of these commodities can also result in slow growth, poverty, and conflict, so these facilities can shut down their operations if prices are low and resume operation when prices are high.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/3565ebe09028d23e0d2c2dc04f0695e1/3d964b71a12eb857